The iconic Chelsea Hotel in New York City was once notorious as a refuge for the eccentric, the eclectic, and the creative.

During the second half of the 20th century it was a hive of creativity that attracted a host of famous and emerging names from the worlds of music, film, literature, art and fashion.

Although the hotel closed for major renovations in 2011, it has been immortalized in countless art forms by many of the artists who made it their home at one stage or another.

