Towards the end of the 20th century it fell out of favor and into disrepair and for many years lived in on its reputation, before the doors closed in 2011 for a gut renovation.

After the hotel was sold, New York-based photographer Victoria Cohen was invited to capture and document the essence of the building’s original interior before its sad demise.

Cohen’s photographs of the hallways, lobbies, and rooms, once beaming with life and vision, but by 2011 bare and aged, help to illuminate a bohemian era that once was, speaking untold truths of a lost time.

